---
title: Spice-Rubbed Pork with a Jammy Glaze over Scallion Couscous and Yellow Squash
description: We’re big fans of pan sauces because they’re an easy way to make a great dish completely irresistible. Here, apricot jam, lemon juice, and tangy mustard mingle with fond—that’s chef speak for those crispy bits left by seared protein—to create a delicious condiment you’ll want to drizzle over everything. Speaking of, we’re serving up sides of chewy Israeli couscous and lightly charred yellow squash for maximum dinnertime deliciousness.
